cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.DC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the performance analysis and optimization of a standalone LTE-U network, which is a wireless communication network. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper discusses the impact of delayed channel state information (CSI) on the network performance. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper proposes a joint optimization of the medium access control (MAC) protocol and CSI feedback scheme to maximize users' energy efficiency while ensuring fair coexistence with Wi-Fi. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible category as the paper considers the downlink throughput of the LTE-U network, which is related to multimedia transmission. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is a less likely category but still possible as the paper proposes decomposition-based low-complexity algorithms for solving the optimization problems.
